description._content: Sydney Exposures book and exhibition caption: Volunteers for war, Ingleburn, November 1939 : The men of the Second AIF were accused of being 'economic conscripts' who had joined up for the sake of 5 shillings a day with food and quarters, rather than remain on the dole of 8 shillings and sixpence a week.
